# =============================================================================
# Open WebUI — environment variable names (placeholder values only)
# =============================================================================
# `backend/.env` was not available to read in this workspace, so keys were
# collected from `backend/open_webui/**/*.py` (`os.environ.get` / `os.getenv`),
# plus a few extras used by `backend/start.sh` / dev scripts or the Vite
# frontend (e.g. VITE_*). Treat this as a full catalog, not a minimal set.
#
# The backend loads `.env` from the repository root by default — see
# `open_webui/env.py` (`load_dotenv(find_dotenv(BASE_DIR / '.env'))`).
# Copy to repo-root `.env` or `backend/.env` depending on how you run the app.
#
# Every value below is the literal placeholder `your_key_here`. Replace with
# real values locally; never commit secrets.
# =============================================================================

